description.narrative: National and state governments have increased capacity for coordination and evidence based policies, planning, implementation and monitoring for equitable, inclusive and risk informed quality education, which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: National and state governments have increased capacity for coordination and evidence based policies, planning, implementation and monitoring for equitable, inclusive and risk informed quality education

description.narrative: Technical support to Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) resulted in strengthening of Education Management Information System (EMIS) and development of Performance Grading Index (PGI) at the national level. Capacity development of state education functionaries in analysis and use of Unified District Information System (UDISE) and National Achievement Survey (NAS) data led to preparation of evidence-based education sector plans in fifteen states . Advocacy and technical support to state governments led to preparation of comprehensive school safety and security guidelines, emergency preparedness and risk informed plans and its integration in teacher training programmes in eight states | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
